<body>

<nav>
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo">Treetop</a>
    <div class="hide-mob" style="display:flex;gap:2rem;align-items:center;">
      <a href="/claude-for-business" class="nav-link">Claude for Business</a>
      <a href="/services" class="nav-link">Services</a>
      <a href="/resources" class="nav-link">Resources</a>
      <a href="/about" class="nav-link">About</a>
    </div>
    <a href="/quiz" class="btn-p" style="padding:0.6rem 1.25rem;font-size:0.78rem;">Take the Gap Assessment &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Claude Fluency · Team Training</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">Most teams have access to Claude.<br/><em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Very few are fluent in it.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Claude Fluency is hands-on training that takes a non-technical team from "I opened it once" to confident, daily use. We teach on your real work, not toy examples, so the habits stick after we leave.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href="/book-a-call" class="btn-p">Book a working session &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/quiz" class="btn-g">Take the Gap Assessment</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<section style="background:#0A1A0A;">
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">The real problem</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Buying licenses is easy.<br/>Changing how people work is not.</h2>
    <p class="body">Most companies that "rolled out AI" bought seats and sent a link. A few enthusiasts use it constantly. Everyone else tried it twice, got a mediocre answer, and quietly went back to the old way. The tool is not the problem. The gap is fluency: knowing what to hand to Claude, how to ask, and how to fold it into the work people already do.</p>
    <div class="grid-4" style="margin-top:2rem;">
      <div class="grid-cell-alt">
        <span class="cell-icon">🤷</span>
        <div class="cell-title">"I don't know what to use it for"</div>
        <div class="cell-desc">People can list AI features but cannot name three tasks in their own week where it would help. We fix that first.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-cell-alt">
        <span class="cell-icon">😐</span>
        <div class="cell-title">"The output was generic"</div>
        <div class="cell-desc">Weak prompts and no context produce bland results. Fluency is mostly about giving Claude the right inputs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-cell-alt">
        <span class="cell-icon">🔒</span>
        <div class="cell-title">"I'm not sure it's safe"</div>
        <div class="cell-desc">Smart professionals hold back until they understand the privacy boundaries. We make the rules clear and practical.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-cell-alt">
        <span class="cell-icon">📉</span>
        <div class="cell-title">"It didn't stick"</div>
        <div class="cell-desc">One webinar changes nothing. Habits form when people use the tool on real work, with support, for a few weeks.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">What it covers</span>
    <h2 class="h2">From curious to confident, on your real work.</h2>
    <div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Find the work worth handing over</div>
          <div class="step-desc">We start with each person's actual week and map the recurring writing, summarizing, and research tasks where Claude earns its keep. Everyone leaves the first session with their own short list.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Prompting and context that actually work</div>
          <div class="step-desc">The difference between a generic answer and a great one is usually context. We teach the simple habits: giving Claude your materials, your voice, and clear instructions, without any jargon.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Projects and reusable workflows</div>
          <div class="step-desc">We set up Claude Projects so your team's best prompts, documents, and standards live in one place and get reused, instead of being retyped from scratch every time.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">04</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Privacy and judgment</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Clear, plain-English rules for what is fine to use Claude for and what is not, so people use it confidently inside the lines your business needs.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">05</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Habits that outlast the training</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Follow-up sessions on real work, a shared prompt library, and a point of contact for questions. The goal is daily use that continues long after the last session.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;padding-top:2.5rem;">
      <a href="/book-a-call" class="btn-p">Book a working session &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/claude-training" class="btn-g">See workflow-specific training &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section style="background:#0A1A0A;">
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Who it is for</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Built for bright, busy, non-technical teams.</h2>
    <p class="body">Professional services firms, finance and operations teams, founders and their leadership, and any group where the people are smart and time-poor but new to Claude. No coding, no prior AI experience required. If you can write an email, you can become fluent.</p>
    <div class="chip-grid">
      <span class="chip">Law &amp; professional services</span>
      <span class="chip">Finance &amp; accounting</span>
      <span class="chip">Operations</span>
      <span class="chip">Founders &amp; execs</span>
      <span class="chip">Marketing &amp; comms</span>
      <span class="chip">Client-facing teams</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <div class="cta-box">
      <div>
        <div class="cta-text">Make your team genuinely fluent.</div>
        <div class="cta-sub">Tell us about your team and we will send a link to book a working session. We will show you exactly what fluency would look like for your group and where to start.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/book-a-call" class="btn-p">Book a working session &rarr;</a>
        <a href="/quiz" class="btn-g">Take the Gap Assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section style="border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;background:#050D05;">
  <div class="sec-inner" style="max-width:780px;">
    <span class="lbl">Related</span>
    <h2 class="h2" style="font-size:clamp(1.5rem,2.8vw,2rem);margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Start here</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;font-size:0.96rem;line-height:1.9;color:#C0D8C0;">
      <li><a href="/claude-for-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Using Claude in business &rarr;</a></li>
      <li><a href="/how-to-set-up-claude-first-time" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">How to set up Claude for the first time &rarr;</a></li>
      <li><a href="/claude-vs-chatgpt-for-knowledge-work" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Claude vs ChatGPT for knowledge work &rarr;</a></li>
      <li><a href="/claude-training" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Workflow-specific Claude training &rarr;</a></li>
      <li><a href="/claude-for-small-business" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3);">Claude for small business &rarr;</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<GlobalFooter />

</body>
</html>
